Group Policy Object

Wallpaper Change For User

Step 1

Tools > Group Policy Management > Select Group Policy Object > Right Click and Select New > Give New GPO Name >
Ok

Step 2

From New GPO Click Right and Select Edit > User Configuration > Policies > Administrative Templetes > Desktop >
Desktop > Desktop Wallpaper > Enable > Create a Folder(Do this on C Drive) > Share this Folder >
Create a Wallpaper and put this wallpaper On shared Folder > Wallpaper Location(Network Path) > 
Link this GPO on destination OU's

Step 3

Go to Run and Type cmd and hit enter > Type gpupdate /force > hit enter > Wait for complete

Step 4

On Clint PC log in that User who are on the destination OU's > Go to Run and Type cmd and hit enter > 
Type gpupdate /force > hit enter > Wait for complete.
